snippet.textDisplay:
My parents have been special needs foster parents for almost 15 years, 40+ placements later and they have adopted 6 very incredible kids. My older sister and I have encouraged and supported them during their journey, and we’ve seen them sacrifice their dream careers and their own goals in the pursuit of loving and supporting kids in need.

Honestly any kind of act would speak volumes to them, I’ve made it my mission going forward in life to show them that they are loved and appreciated and that they make a difference. I’ve watched them have mental breakdowns, and watched the courts and foster care system work against them while they’ve worked so hard without a break. I know that anything you guys could do , regardless of finances, would go miles towards showing them that they matter and that they’ve made a huge difference in this world.

Instagram: @wildestrengthrj
#YesFam

snippet.textDisplay:
In the hope of you seeing this...

Im back on in the efforts to really have Yes Theory acknowledge Camp Del Corazon and help out an amazing organization as much as possible by using the winnings from the Mr. Beast Hide & Seek Challenge to produce a Yes Theory styled video about / with Camp Del Corazon.

Reason I'm back on here in the comment section, even after a week of the video being up, is because I am passionate about Yes Theory as well as DEEPLY passionate about Camp Del Corazon.
Being that so much has been going on lately from a virus that has been going around worldwide and it pretty much affecting Everyone & Everything in someway shape or form I also just had to hop back on here. Camp Del Corazon, for example, has had to cancel a few up coming events, some of which include fundraiser and social gatherings that make Camp Del Corazon what is it. Also, being that Camp Del Corazon caters to the Congenital Heart Defect community this pandemic has also just been a very tough crazy situation to be going through as a community.

I know Yes Theory is legit capable of legit anything & everything, I do believe that for sure. If there's ANY way this message gets to you guys just please listen... Camp Del Corazon Deserves a shot. I'm not saying they deserve the winnings, but they deserve at least a shot. Please, use the winning to come up with something amazing, to plan for a great way to help, to do research on this amazing organization, and to give Camp Del Corazon a Yes Theory shot.


Until I hear about what you guys have done with the winning, I will write back. I'm passionate, and nothing can take that away from me. Not even a virus haha.

snippet.textDisplay: Hi, I am a 17 year old High School student from central Scotland. After finishing school this year I had partnered up with a charity called Project Trust, which sends recent school leavers abroad for a year to teach english to underprivileged children in developing countries. The country I would be going to is Honduras, which is perfect for me as the national language is Spanish and due to my dads Spanish heritage I speak fluent Spanish, the condition for the charity is that you need to fundraise £6200, this is to be done by the end of June, I was perfectly on track having just over £3000 at the end of February. I had planned a ceilidh and a coffee morning for my local community, which I was going to advertise through my second job where I make up the paper rounds for my town, by sliding leaflets in all the newspapers. All the proceeds I made from this were going towards a Kiltwalk, which is essentially a 23mile walk in a kilt (which you could do with me?). My issue is due to the recent coronavirus, I have had to cancel my upcoming events as it is too dangerous for the elderly members of the community. Therefore, I was wondering if you would be able to help me in any way? Love from Erik in Scotland
